name: old yin
description: This line type represents a yin line (negative, yielding, broken) that is in motion, in transition to becoming a yang line. The value given to this line type is 6 (the sum of the value of all three coins showing yin).

name: young yin
description: This line type represents a yin line (negative, yielding, broken) that is not in motion, still and at rest. The value given to this line type is 8 (the sum of the value of one coin showing yin and two coins showing yang).

name: old yang
description: This line type represents a yang line (positive, firm, unbroken) that is in motion, in transition to becoming a yin line. The value given to this line type is 9 (the sum of the value of all three coins showing yang).

name: young yang
description: This line type represents a yang line (positive, firm, unbroken) that is not in motion, still and at rest. The value given to this line type is 7 (the sum of the value of two coins showing yin and one coin showing yang).
